\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {11.1}{\ignorespaces \xpg@aux {}{english}\ignorespaces 16-QAM Rayleigh fading --- BER vs.~SNR for all 48 neural relay variants and two classical baselines (AF, DF) with 95\% confidence intervals. The plot reveals a dense cluster of neural variants between the AF and DF curves, with the best variants approaching AF performance at high SNR.}}{114}{figure.caption.122}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {11.2}{\ignorespaces \xpg@aux {}{english}\ignorespaces Top-3 neural relay architectures compared against AF and DF for 16-QAM in Rayleigh fading. All three best-performing variants use input LayerNorm (+LN) without CSI injection.}}{115}{figure.caption.123}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {11.3}{\ignorespaces \xpg@aux {}{english}\ignorespaces 16-PSK Rayleigh fading --- BER vs.~SNR for all 48 neural relay variants and two classical baselines. The neural variants form a tighter cluster than QAM16, reflecting the constant-envelope nature of PSK which reduces the amplitude-aliasing challenge.}}{116}{figure.caption.124}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {11.4}{\ignorespaces \xpg@aux {}{english}\ignorespaces Top-3 neural relay architectures compared against AF and DF for 16-PSK in Rayleigh fading. In contrast to QAM16, all three best-performing PSK16 variants use CSI injection (+CSI or +CSI+LN).}}{117}{figure.caption.125}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {11.5}{\ignorespaces \xpg@aux {}{english}\ignorespaces Training loss (MSE) and accuracy for Mamba-2 (+LN scaled\_tanh). The model converges within approximately 5 epochs and stabilises, with validation accuracy closely tracking training accuracy --- indicating minimal overfitting.}}{117}{figure.caption.126}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {11.6}{\ignorespaces \xpg@aux {}{english}\ignorespaces Training loss and accuracy for Mamba S6 (+CSI tanh). The CSI-augmented input produces a smooth, monotonic training convergence, with the additional channel-state feature providing clear gradient signal for the optimizer.}}{118}{figure.caption.127}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {11.7}{\ignorespaces \xpg@aux {}{english}\ignorespaces Training loss and accuracy for Transformer (+CSI sigmoid). The Transformer exhibits rapid initial convergence (within 3 epochs) followed by a flat plateau, characteristic of the attention mechanism's ability to capture input structure quickly.}}{118}{figure.caption.128}%
